Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with lexicon extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the purview of cs.CL. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper proposes new models to better capture semantic information and select optimal translation pairs, which are relevant to information retrieval tasks such as cross-lingual search and document translation. 
3. cs.LG (Learning) - The paper proposes new models that extend the scope of topic models and incorporate probability-based selection, which are relevant to machine learning and probabilistic modeling. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes new models that address challenges in applying topic models to non-parallel data, which are relevant to the broader field of AI and its applications in NLP. 
5. cs.DL (Deep Learning) - The paper proposes new models that incorporate deep learning techniques to better capture semantic information, which are relevant to the subfield of deep learning in NLP.
